Important information

Safety Information

If you are pregnant or lactating, have any health condition or are taking any medication, consult your health professional before use.

Indications

Pure Encapsulations - Magnesium (citrate) 180's

Ingredients

Each serving size (1 vegetarian capsule) contains: Magnesium (as magnesium citrate) 150 mg. Other ingredients: Vegetarian capsule (cellulose, water), ascorbyl palmitate.

Directions

As a dietary supplement, take 1-4 capsules daily. Consume with food.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

[It is to be expected that you may have to take more for your body to realize the full benefits.]

I will find out if there is any apparent difference [An UPDATE is available below in this review re: my experience with the NOW Magnesium Citrate].

That "said," I want to emphasize that I am happy with the results of taking Magnesium Citrate - I sleep much better, have no muscle cramping, and in general feel more relaxed. If the Pure Encapsulations Magnesium Citrate were not so expensive I would rate this product at five stars.

It is my understanding (from the Pure Encapsulations site) that Pure Encapsulations is a company that sells to MDs and medical professionals who are interested in selling vitamins to their clients. Nothing wrong with that - just a pricier product to the consumer.

What some people still may not be aware of is that a lot of vitamin companies buy their vitamins from stock wholesalers and then package and promote those products under their own label, etc. The same is true of most cosmetics -in which case you are buying their fragrance added and colorants, perhaps some Vit. E and/or aloe extract, etc. - and this I know from personal business experience in the industry. Very few vitamin companies or cosmetic companies actually make their own products.

There are some very reputable, high quality vitamins available for much less than "designer" vitamins, which I consider Pure Encapsulations to be. I think Pure Encapsulations supplements are good, I just think there are lower priced vitamins available that are just as good. Perhaps Amazon will let me mention that I think that NOW Vitamins are just as high quality as Pure Encapsulations at a much more reasonable price.

UPDATE:

I have been taking the  Now Foods Magnesium Citrate 200mg, 250 Tablets , which is pure magnesium citrate for months now and find that it is working very well - certainly as well and possibly even better than the Pure Encapsulations brand, but definitely without diminished effectiveness. Do be sure an check the label / content information (which are not always available on Amazon, and would require additional research online at the vitamin company's site and then making sure you are getting the same product by comparing the bar code numbers - an inconvenience but worth the effort). The link in this comment for Now Foods Magnesium Citrate 200mg, 250 Tablets  does include complete images of the label (which can be enlarged for easy reading) so you can see that this item only contains Magnesium Citrate.
